  "body": "Two tests cases failing from ethereum\\tests for EIP-3860:\r\n- stEIP3860.create2InitCodeSizeLimit_d1g0v0_invalid_Merge+3860\r\n- stEIP3860.createInitCodeSizeLimit_d1g0v0_invalid_Merge+3860\r\n\r\nRoot cause is:\r\n- gas cost of CREATE/CREATE2 operations when init code size is exceeded, currently none is taken, but it is expected to deduct full cost\r\n- nonce increment, currently nonce is not incremented prior to return\r\n\r\n**To Reproduce**\r\nSteps to reproduce the behavior:\r\n1. Run stEIP3860.create2InitCodeSizeLimit_d1g0v0_invalid_Merge+3860 test\r\n1. Run stEIP3860.createInitCodeSizeLimit_d1g0v0_invalid_Merge+3860 test\r\n\r\n**Expected behavior**\r\n- full gas cost of CREATE/CREATE2 opcode should be deducted when 3860 init code size limit is exceeded\r\n- nonce should be incremented when 3860 init code size limit is exceeded\r\n\r\n**Additional context**\r\nThere may be some future changes to EIP-3860, where this behaviour might be changes\r\n",
